24/10/2016

INSTALL MANUAL

Step 1. Create a new user
    >>>useradd [username]
    >>>passwd [username]

Step 2. Change to root user
    >>>su
    >>>[enter password]
    
Step 3. Create three shell script files in the bin folder named custom_shell.sh,custom_shell_date.sh,custom_shell_ud.sh
    >>>nano custom_shell.sh
    >>>nano custom_shell_date.sh
    >>>nano custom_shell_ud.sh

Step 4. Copy the bash code in the screenshots provided to the appropriote, save and exit.

Step 5. Change the running shell for the new user from bash to the custom shell.
    >>>chsh -s /bin/custom_shell.sh
    
    
The new users shell is now the custom shell with limited functionality.

